<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">March 18, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-march-18-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-234470 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ana-Mendieta_169-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://themillions.com/2024/03/xochitl-gonzalez-wants-to-reframe-art-history.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Xochitl Gonzalez on Ana Mendieta and art history</span></a></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400"> </span><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/11/t-magazine/gay-best-friends.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mark Harris on the Gay Best Friend</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://thepointmag.com/dialogue/a-form-of-refuge/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ursula Lindsey and Atef Alshaer on literature and Gaza</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-march-18-2024/"><button>More News</button></a>

